
{center}
{subhead} Inexpensive Internet In The U.K.{def}{p}
Article by Chris Seward
{left}
{p} {p}

Introduction:
{p} {p}
Welcome to this small guide. If you don't know what it is then please
let me explain...
{p} {p}
... This guide is a small text on how to go about setting up your Amiga
for use with Free dot Net, an internet provider that does not currently
have any support for the Amiga computer.
{p} {p}
{p} {p}
Information about FDN:
{p} {p}
Free dot Net is a UK based internet company that is very inexpensive compared
to most other internet companys. You may be wondering why they keep the
costs so low? Well they offer many different packages so you only get
what you want, with many internet providers you are paying for things that
you do not always use, below I'll explain a little about each package
available.
{p} {p}
{p} {p}
Standard Service - Connection Charge £30
{p} {p}
Package includes :-
{p} {p}
- Two years unlimited access time to the Internet
{p} {p}
- Full use of Web Browser, FTP, Archie, Gopher, Telnet, IRC.
{p} {p}
- Help lines open Monday to Friday - 9am-6pm.
{p} {p}
This package DOES NOT include web space, email or news group access.
{p} {p}
{p} {p}
Gold Service - Connection Charge £40
{p} {p}
- Two years unlimited access time to the Internet.
{p} {p}
- Full use of Web Browser, FTP, Archie, Gopher, Telnet, IRC and Public
Facing Unsupported News Service
{p} {p}
- Help lines open 7 days a week.
{p} {p}
This package DOES NOT include web space or email access.
{p} {p}
{p} {p}
Platinum Service - Connection Charge £75
{p} {p}
- Five years unlimited access time to the Internet.
{p} {p}
- Full use of Web Browser, FTP, Archie, Gopher, Telnet, IRC and Public
Facing Unsupported News Service
{p} {p}
- Help lines open 7 days a week.
{p} {p}
This package DOES NOT include web space or email access.
{p} {p}
{p} {p}
Extra Services
{p} {p}
Email, £50 per year, address will be : <ANYTHING>@thefree.net
{p} {p}
Web space, £10 setup charge and £10 per year for space.
{p} {p}
{p} {p}
Basic System required:
{p} {p}
A500/600, 2mb ram, HardDrive, modem.
{p} {p}
{p} {p}
Recommended System:
{p} {p}
A1200, 68030 processor, 16mb ram, HardDrive, 33/56bps modem.
{p} {p}
{p} {p}
Where to get your software:
{p} {p}
Unfortunally because Free dot Net don't support the Amiga (yet.) you
will be presented with PC and MAC software, you'll have get the Amiga
software for yourself. There are many ways to do this, first check
out Amiga magazine cover CD's like those found on the Amiga Format.
You will beable to find most of the software there, if you have access
to the internet already or have a way of accessing the internet then
below is where you can find all the required files. These are all
Demo/Trial software packages and have restrictions if not registered.
{p} {p}
ALL URL are web pages and these can be accessed by a web browser
{p} {p}
ALL Aminet are ftp sites and can be accessed by going to
wuarchive.wustl.edu - via an FTP package
{p} {p}
{p} {p}
